        <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
            <h2>Edmund is a very hungry llama.<br/>You might say he's the hungriest llama.</h2>
            <p>The problem is that he's very picky. Llamas can be total divas. Somedays he only likes fruit. Others
                he only likes red fruit. Sometimes he'll eat anything with cheese except pizza.</p>
            <p>The good news is Edmund will tell you exactly what he wants.</p>
            <p>The bad news is he will only do so using logic diagrams.</p>
            <h3>Wait. What?</h3>
            <p>Logic diagrams are used by engineers to describe how circuits work. You can learn more about the
                different logic symbols on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logic_gate">Wikipedia</a>, of course.</p>
            <h3>How to Play</h3>
            <p>For each question, you will see a logic diagram describing what Edmund wants to eat. Underneath the logic diagram are several food items. You can toggle each tasty snack on and off by clicking it. Your goal is to choose which foods Edmund will eat. The first player to correctly select the correct food and click submit gets 100 points and we all move on to the next question.</p>
        </div>                  
